Depends on the specifics.<br>
<br>
Player with corpse runs up and says, &quot;Can you rez corpse here please?&quot; Cleric is fine on mana, goes hocus pocus, and the player donates 100 pp.  No worries.<br>
<br>
/ooc Corpse_01 says Need a rez at XYZ<br>
/g Cleric_01 says Okay if I go do this?<br>
/g Group says Sure, go for it.<br>
No worries.<br>
<br>
/ooc Looking for rez at XYZ.  Will donate 100 pp.<br>
/g Cleric_01 says, &quot;BRB&quot;<br>
(shock at this as said cleric ignored other rez requests but jumps at the one with the money tag on it)<br>
(minutes pass...cleric returns)<br>
/g Puller_02 says, &quot;Mana check.&quot;<br>
/g Cleric_01 says, &quot;OOM&quot;<br>
and we see none of that 100 pp, oh yeah, I mind.<br>
(true example)<br>
<br>
My cause today (see the &quot;It's just a game&quot; thread) is player courtesy.  No one person's game experience is more important than any other.  If the cleric grinds an entire group to a halt so that he or she can run off, let us cool our heals for 5 minutes while doing the rez and collecting fee, make us all wait another 5 minutes so they can get back up to decent mana, and then KEEP the 100 pp, that's selfish and rude.  Even if they split the 100 plat, it might still be pretty rude.<br>
<br>
And yes, I have disbanded clerics out of groups for doing this repeatedly (after warning in /tell).  Don't think I can't live without you.  I've been in plenty of profitable (XP and PP-wise) groups without a cleric. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p>Salenie Mithrilweaver<BR>Proud Member of <a href=" http://www.clanbattleaxe.com">Clan Battle Axe</a><BR>Ally of Vivix Protectorate<BR>Koada'dal, Magician, Grandmaster Smith, and Master of All Languages<BR>RL life pending...</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#666666><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub4.ezboard.com/uspycewrack.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Spyce Wrack</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Veteran</span><br>  Posts: 131<br> <font color=#E9D756>(2/8/02 2:16:33 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub4.ezboard.com/femarrdragonsandplanes.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2999.topic&index=24>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Rogues - gotta love em :P</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> I was in LoIO when Meblo got booted from his group for pickpocketing<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
